**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

*   **Count & Layers:** The structure appears to have 20 blocks and 3 layers in some areas and 2 layers in others.
*   **Spatial Relationships:**
    *   The bottom layer is primarily composed of arch-shaped blocks (index 1 & 2).
    *   On the left side, a red arch (index 1) forms the base, supporting a yellow rectangular block (index 10), and then a green block (index 4), and an orange angled block (index 16). There's also a green block (index 9) supporting a blue block (index 3) and an orange block (index 5).
    *   In the middle section, two yellow half-cylinder blocks (index 13) are used.
    *   On the right side, there's a red arch (index 2) as the base. Above it is a vertical green block (index 9), a yellow vertical block (index 11), and an orange rectangular block (index 15). There's a blue cube (index 3) and another vertical green block (index 9).
